{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"body":"## A3 LIVE remediation — ops note (2026-07-08)\n\n**Store:** shared `tickets` branch (origin/tickets). **Tool:** `rebar fsck --repair` (this worktree's local build, incl. the reconciler in-flight guard).\n\n### Before → After (fsck fault counts)\n| Fault class | Before | After | Disposition |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| SNAPSHOT_INCONSISTENT | 2422 | **0** | auto-retired (rename folded source → `.retired`); incl. 4 folded-OLDER-snapshot cases fixed this pass |\n| ORPHAN_EVENT | 13 | 13 | HUMAN-TRIAGE (all order-sensitive EDIT); left surfaced, NOT auto-written |\n| MISSING_CREATE | 1 | 1 | HUMAN-TRIAGE; surfaced, never auto-written |\n\nResult pushed to origin/tickets @ `47d917f6`. Auto-recoverable classes → **zero**.\n\n### Reconciler safety\n- Disabled `reconcile-bridge.yml` for the window; **re-enabled** after (now `active`).\n- The in-flight guard correctly ABORTED an initial attempt while a live pass held `refs/reconciler/lock` (the pass was heartbeating). Waited for the pass to finish, then ran cleanly.\n- Pre-tag `pre-a3-remediation` written before any write (rollback point).\n\n### Tooling gap found + fixed\n`_repair_plan` excluded every `*-SNAPSHOT.json` from retire candidates, so a re-compaction that folds an OLDER snapshot into a newer one's `source_event_uuids` left the still-present older snapshot as an unrepaired SNAPSHOT_INCONSISTENT (4 tickets: 72d5, b043, ce94, fc9e). Fixed: older snapshots are now retire candidates (never the horizon `latest_snap`), with a unit test.\n\n### Human-triage disposition (empirically validated — the plan's routing is CORRECT)\nThe 13 ORPHAN_EVENTs are all pre-snapshot **EDIT** events (assignee edits) absent from `source_event_uuids`. I tested the deterministic full-log rebuild (`--repair-snapshots`) on them and **it CORRUPTED state**: 11 of 13 tickets flipped `closed → in_progress` (the rebuild reorders STATUS events). **Reverted before any push** — no bad data reached origin. This confirms EDIT orphans must stay HUMAN-TRIAGE (auto-rebuild is unsafe), exactly as the A3 orphan-disposition constant routes them. Follow-up ticket filed for manual reconciliation."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1783552642421278001,"uuid":"8d24e059-b152-4afd-950a-175dbbe7048b"}